31271362, "span": {"begin": 466, "end": 505}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:255738"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "NARC-1", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.991492748260498, "span": {"begin": 507, "end": 513}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:255738"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "PCSK9", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9926354289054871, "span": {"begin": 559, "end": 564}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3949"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "low density lipoprotein receptor", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9983189105987549, "span": {"begin": 574, "end": 606}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3949"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "LDLR", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9929571151733398, "span": {"begin": 608, "end": 612}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "liver cells", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.8781888484954834, "span": {"begin": 632, "end": 643}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3949"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "LDLR", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9932382106781006, "span": {"begin": 677, "end": 681}}, {"id": ["mesh:D002784"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "cholesterol", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9987438321113586, "span": {"begin": 706, "end": 717}}], "text": "Proprotein convertase subtilisin/kexin type 9 (PCSK9) is primarily expressed in the liver (Seidah et al. 2014). &nbsp;PCSK9 has an important role in lipid uptake regulation. &nbsp;Sterol Regulatory Element Binding Proteins (SREBPs) regulate transcription rates, increasing protein expression of proprotein convertase subtilisin/kexin type 9 (PCSK9; Lambert et al. 2006; Seidah et al. 2014). &nbsp;Proprotein convertase subtilisin/kexin type 9 is also referred to as Neural Apoptosis-Regulated Convertase-1 (NARC-1; Horton et al. 2003; Benjannet et al. 2004). PCSK9 binds to low density lipoprotein receptor (LDLR) on the surface of liver cells, resulting in the degradation of LDLR and decreased uptake of cholesterol (Poirier et al. 2008; Seidah et al. 2014).", "timestamp": "Fri May 15 22:01:08 +0000 2026"}